    "Moreover, we find that in some cases (e.g., \"3C\" for zero filling and \"1C\" for t-READi), t-READi can achieve comparable performance with zero filling with fewer camera sensors.",
    "The result shows that fewer sensors can be used by t-READi to achieve the same performance than previous solutions, thus proving t-READi's better efficiency. b) Missing lidar.",
    ": We then demonstrate t-READi's robustness to missing lidar.",
    "As Figure 13(a) and 13(b) show, removing the lidar and filling the missing modality with 0's renders the system unusable since it only gives an mAP and NDS of 0.22 and 0.29, respectively.",
    "The poor performance can be attributed to the fact that lidar is the dominant sensor and removing it results in major information loss."
